This paper involves natural language processing and statistical methods to analyze Twitter data, which suggests it belongs to the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the use of unsupervised machine learning and Fourier analysis indicates a focus on machine learning (cs.SI) and signal processing (cs.SD). The study also involves identifying emergent language communities and operational characteristics, which could fall under the categories of cyber security (cs.CR) and complex systems (cs.CY).
